  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Slice the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619779405773-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619779405773-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619779405773-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619779405773-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1619779405773-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> potato discs</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Spread the <strong>potato discs</strong> into a single layer and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy – these are your <strong>salt & pepper slices</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619779434844-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619779434844-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619779434844-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619779434844-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1619779434844-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4] </span>slices from the <strong>tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> and set these aside for later</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining tomato </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619779482472-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619779482472-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619779482472-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619779482472-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1619779482472-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot  with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped tomato</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to break down</p><p>Once the tomato has started to break down, add the <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 10-15 min, stirring frequently, or until thickened to a jam-like consistency – this is your <strong>warming tomato jam</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1619779500429-x200.jpg",
